The Jamaican bobsled team are now headed to another Olympics after the Sochi Organizing Committee offered to cover the travel costs for the team.

Olympic organizers said Saturday that Jamaica has qualified for the two-man competition at next month's Games, and later announced that they will help meet some but not all of the team’s financial needs.

The team- which shot to popularity following the release of Cool Runnings, the 1993 film based on their story to make it from their tropical island nation to the slopes of the 1988 winter Olympics- is still trying to raise money to pay for the equipment they will need to compete.

