Winston Watts, the sled driver, confirmed today that they are still raising money but has not said how much they need. On Saturday, he estimated they needed $80,000 but that included the cost of travel.

He said he has received calls from countless people around the world offering financial support.

For a nation lacking bobsled tradition, or snowy winters, Jamaica has often fared quite well on the international circuits.

